terized the history of modern Korea, this is the story of a struggle toward healing, unity, and perhaps a reconciliation between love and hatred.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUHP eBook Package 2000-2013z978311056414340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082483794540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824837945423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780824837945.jpg  a978-3-11-056414-3  UHP eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK